                            <comment id="16080653" author="githubbot" created="Mon, 10 Jul 2017 17:04:09 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;GitHub user dguy opened a pull request:&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;    &lt;a href=&quot;https://github.com/apache/kafka/pull/3516&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow noopener&quot;&gt;https://github.com/apache/kafka/pull/3516&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;    &lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/KAFKA-5562&quot; title=&quot;Do streams state directory cleanup on a single thread&quot; class=&quot;issue-link&quot; data-issue-key=&quot;KAFKA-5562&quot;&gt;&lt;del&gt;KAFKA-5562&lt;/del&gt;&lt;/a&gt;: execute state dir cleanup on single thread&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;    Use a single `StateDirectory` per streams instance.&lt;br/&gt;
    Use threadId to determine which thread owns the lock.&lt;br/&gt;
    Only allow the owning thread to unlock.&lt;br/&gt;
    Execute cleanup on a scheduled thread in `KafkaStreams`&lt;/p&gt;

